column5: I will be going to Corwall in a week from now and I am so excited that I was sitting in my boat last night looking over the map of Lake St.Francis for areas that I consider to hold Muskies. Waypoints were marked and I have to do now is wait for the 24th to roll around.  I will be there from Saturday the 25th until the 29th or 30th. I have plans to fish with my brother on the 25 th and 26th but I am free from the 27th to the 29th. If anyone wants to hop in with me on any of those days you are most welocme to join me. Send me a PM with your phone number and I will make every attempt to hook up with you.  Pete
There's an offer I wish I could accept. Come up this way instead and I'll join you for sure Pete. Good luck (and I see I'm not the only one who sits in his boat in the garage)
I only wish I had a garage .I sit in mine in the pouring rain.But that is a great offer.
great offer  hope you catch lots
TB, I never received a post brotha. No worries, Lew is going to join me on Francis for the 2 days. Come on 59 incher. 6 more sleeps.
Two experienced guys, nice piece of water and a great time of the year. You both will do well for sure! Good luck to you.
Pete I hope ya have great time up there and the weather man works out for ya
Good luck to you and Lew, Pete !!!  That's the lake I learned to fish !!
It'll be a good couple of days Pete.  Gimme a call at home when you get the motel info and I'll see you down there next Monday.
I hope with this build-up, one of you will post some sort of report!
Have fun, stay warm, and wear 2 PFDs!!!
If Pete gets his 59"er, Rich, I'm pretty sure there'll be a report
not sure hwat happened with the PM but you are better off with Lew for sure  good luck guys  TB
